From: Mikhail Gavrilov <mikhail.v.gavrilov@gmail.com>
Date: Fri, 8 May 2026 00:00:00 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] Bluetooth: btmtk: handle FUNC_CTRL events without status field

Some MediaTek controllers (MT7922/MT7921) respond to WMT_FUNC_CTRL with
a truncated event that lacks the status field. Commit 634a4408c061
("Bluetooth: btmtk: validate WMT event SKB length before struct access")
added a strict sizeof check that rejects these responses with -EINVAL,
breaking Bluetooth initialization.

Fix by defaulting to BTMTK_WMT_ON_UNDONE when the status field is absent,
matching the effective pre-regression behavior.

BugLink: https://bugzilla.kernel.org/show_bug.cgi?id=221511
Fixes: 634a4408c061 ("Bluetooth: btmtk: validate WMT event SKB length before struct access")
Signed-off-by: Mikhail Gavrilov <mikhail.v.gavrilov@gmail.com>
---
 drivers/bluetooth/btmtk.c | 6 ++++--
 1 file changed, 4 insertions(+), 2 deletions(-)

diff --git a/drivers/bluetooth/btmtk.c b/drivers/bluetooth/btmtk.c
index f70c1b0f8990..fb4875760164 100644
--- a/drivers/bluetooth/btmtk.c
+++ b/drivers/bluetooth/btmtk.c
@@ -719,8 +719,10 @@ static int btmtk_usb_hci_wmt_sync(struct hci_dev *hdev,
 	case BTMTK_WMT_FUNC_CTRL:
 		if (!skb_pull_data(data->evt_skb,
 				   sizeof(wmt_evt_funcc->status))) {
-			err = -EINVAL;
-			goto err_free_skb;
+			bt_dev_dbg(hdev,
+				   "FUNC_CTRL event without status, assuming UNDONE");
+			status = BTMTK_WMT_ON_UNDONE;
+			break;
 		}
 
 		wmt_evt_funcc = (struct btmtk_hci_wmt_evt_funcc *)wmt_evt;
-- 
2.54.0
